al broad discovery call missed Tavily entirely, requiring a focused recovery call.","Raw search responses were large, around 9k to 12k tokens per search call, even with highlights and text budgets.","Batch fetches produced very large raw responses despite `maxCharacters`, which reduced context-budget predictability.","Fetch responses normalized to zero evidence entries in the harness, so search-normalized evidence was more useful than fetch-normalized evidence."],"notableFailures":["Direct fix, needs no further changes: the first attempted call failed locally because the args file was created relative to the wrong workspace; the accidental file was moved to trash and the args were recreated under /Users/ethanaggor/firecrawl-results/evals/work.","Direct fix, needs no further changes: broad discovery did not return Tavily; a targeted docs.tavily.com query recovered the missing provider evidence.","Fixed but could benefit from cleaner/simpler implementation with an architectural change: web_fetch_exa did not provide predictable context budgeting in this batch trajectory and returned much larger raw responses than requested.","Fixed but could benefit from cleaner/simpler implementation with an architectural change: harness normalization for fetch calls produced no normalized evidence, making final evidence accounting depend on search normalization and raw fetch text."],"confidence":0.84},"artifact":"report.json"}
